spanGrp.span: Recorded by Maïa Ponsonnet, with video handled by Mathieu Rabusseau, on the morning of 23dr of July 2010, in Larrambi-no near Weemol, with Maggie Tukumba. Initial transcript (tx@) by Maïa Ponsonnet, April 2011.
nunda nunh kanunh Larrambi-no yalah-yin nahdabera kanh wah kah-kolh-bon kanunh
This is Larrambi-no, as we call it, this water is flowing that way there.
nunda nunh kanunh Larrambi-no yala-h-yin nahdabera kanh wah ka-h-kolh-bo-n kanunh
DEM DEM DEM place.name-3sgPOSS 1pl.excl-R-say/do:PR there DEM water 3sg-R-water-go-PR DEM
Weemol Spring, the water hole where the kids go swimming.
check possibly yurrkkang cf DD yurrkku = adv. straight, so considering what the team had been before, yurrkkan could be go passed something (without stopping)
that's where I showed you the sign today,
sainbod for sign post MT had showed MP and M. Rabusseau a sacred tree/place sign confirmed MT220511
kahnidjabeh wah kah-kolh-bon nahdjarrada berru-yirrh kah-kolh-yowmu nahdah
The water come from there, to here, moving down, it flows here.
kahnidjabeh wah ka-h-kolh-bo-n nahdjarrada berru-yirrh ka-h-kolh-yow-mu nahdah
You see there, the water is flowing.
marruh mah kah-bon nunh wah kenbo
Where does this water go then?
?A big female one that holds us there,
MT220511 im sodoba servant im gibit mibala wada ebribodi
This water goes ooon, there to Mount Catt.
new entry menked = place name, outstation, right turn some kilometers before Weemol when coming from Katherine
This water there now, it comes up to Mount Catt,
bah kahke Mobarn mak ka-bobon Mobarn
But it doesn't go to Mobarn.
MT220511 MT220511 bawurryih = barrabbonda kah-kolh-lakmu (Barrabbonda =Emu Spring)
it has its own water that was made there.
MT220511 djarng bla Mobbarn ; Northern nailtailed wallaby.
DD has Nail tail ""organ grinder"" wallaby"; wularla may also be the "ritual" name of the ngorlomorro species, as many species have two names in this way.
Yeah, in Mobarn, that's where it is, on its own.
i.e. in a different part of the country from what we were talking before.
This one is on its own,
The one in Larrambi-no, that we are talking about.
Oh yeah this is a sacred site.
manjh njel kah-kolh-ngabbun kahnunh nahbeng Komdjilin-no
this creature/snake gives us water, this one from Komdjilin-no.
manjh njel ka-h-kolh-ngabbu-n kahnunh nahbeng Komdjilin-no
MT220511 dat woda im gibit mibala brom dat pleis na
The ritual name of dadbu, the king brown. The sign post at Komdjilin-no signals a sacred site which sanctions the presence of dadbarrangkurl.
The king brown. The big snake.
From there, it gives us water,
bah nadjarrerda kah-dja-kolh-yowmu nahdah kah-bon yirrh
but here it keeps flowing, it goes down there.
bah nadjarrerda ka-h-dja-kolh-yow-mu nahdah ka-h-bo-n yirrh
MT220511 it passes here and keeps going
Down there and it comes out to Mount Catt.
marrûh mah djah-yih Mount Catt Dalabon-walung
How do you say Mount Catt in Dalabon?
Or [part of] it goes to Barrabbonda.
MT220511 haf im go barrabboda (im split) new entry barrbbonda, place name, out station c. 80 km from Weemol on the way to Nhulunbuy
I though Mount Catt was in English.
Look this one whatyucallit it's flowering.
This one it really has a lot of flowers look over there.
These damurd flowers are flowering over there.
These flowers that you see, kobokobo
The flowers, kobokobo, that water lilies flowers.
wirrimah nunh kanh kobokobo yalah-lng-yin dat
Or that one kobokobo we also say, that
wirrimah nunh kanh kobokobo yala-h-lng-yin dat
kanh ko-no nidjarra kobo-no nunh dayarr dah-nan mahkih
The flowers here, you see the pindanus too...
MT may want to bring new information to what MP seems to know already.
The four ancestors who created everything.
The Nakorrkkoh are two men and their wives. The dual indicates that MT considers that the men were the main actors in creation.
These are not pindanus, but men.
These, whatsit, they put these here.
check new sense ? DD has mardaddubba = tall grass, but I know it as a clan name for Nayunghyungkih people
They put it here these ones.
biyi nunda dj-- kanh kah-- kah-njon-di
These are men, these, this bunch standing here,
kahnunda Mardardubba Kurrmadjmadja kanunhda burrah-yunginj Nakorrkkoh
There are the Mardardubba and the Kurrmadjamadja people, the two Nakorrkkoh put them here.
kahnunda Mardardubba Kurrmadjmadja kanunhda burra-h-yu-nginj Nakorrkkoh
new entry kurrmadjmadja check meaning. I know of it as a clan name of Nayunghyungki people
MT220511 dubala bin trebelin brom noth brom kolben (crocker island)
they were coming from the north there.
Croker Island kanidjah wadda burrah-bawong kanh Nakorrkkoh
Croker Island, there is the home they left behing, these Nakorrkkoh.
Croker Island kanidjah wadda burra-h-ba-wong kanh Nakorrkkoh
place.name place.name DEM camp 3du>3-R-leave-PP DEM ancestors
Croker Island, where Wurrudjdja is, north of Weemol/Larrambi-no
oh mak-- o wirrimah Kalidjan Kamanj
or, not-- or Kalidjan Kamanj [MT has heard the story many times before]
With their wives, they took them along.
bunu burrah-kaninj nukah kahnidja Wurrudjdja-be balah-bong kahnidja
They brought them two here from Wurrudjdja, they went there,
bunu burra-h-ka-ninj nukah kahnidja Wurrudjdja-be bala-h-bo-ng kahnidja
skin name of one of the Nakorrkkoh
check new entry ? place name ? DD has warlang "ghost bat"
woh kanh balkkan kah-wodnang kanidjah kahnunh
Yeah, when he threw the boomerang, then there,
woh kanh balkkan ka-h-wodna-ng kanidjah kahnunh
wah kanidjah kah-lng-kolh-monwong kanidjah Kul-- Kulmi-no
then he made this water there, Kulmi-no.
MT220511 the water was there but the boomerang shaped it
The two young women are standing there.
Referring to two sacred trees near Kulmi-no billabong (also signalled by a sign) who are the Nakorrkkoh's wives, Kalidjan and Kamanj.
kahnidjah balah-worhdi bunu-karn mah Bulanj Kodjok
They are standing there, each one on his own, Bulanj and Kodjok
kahnidjah bala-h-worhdi bunu-karn mah Bulanj Kodjok
MT220511 bunu karnmah / (The men keep traveling after Kulmi-no, only the wives stand there.)
This is different from other versions.
Them two didn't keep goiing, they're (all) standing there,
Kodjok and Bulanj, they're standing there.
In the djabbanmani-no, the forked tree, they are up there, they (two)...
DD djabbanmani-no = forked tree of ceremonial significance; DD warddi: be on top
MT220511 dubala bin sidan bla openimap dat ding
There, they're moving, they're moving, over there.
There they're hanging, ?that's what they did.
bah nunda kanhdah wah kah-dja-kolh-yowmu munguyh
And there the water just keeps flowing all the time.
bah nunda kanhdah wah ka-h-dja-kolh-yow-mu munguyh
? probably as opposed to stopping at some point in the season?
kanh Komdjilin-no-walung njel kah-ngabbun kanh drimin
From Komdjilin-no, where the dreaming/totem provides us with it,
kanh Komdjilin-no-walung njel ka-h-ngabbu-n kanh drimin
the dadbarrangkurl (king brown), with the python.
new entry ? can't find kurridjardu in DD - a division related to patri-moities scars symbolism. Kurridjardu is King Brown. See the DD intro, Maddock 1974 in Mankind.
